'''Ekphonetic notation''' consists of symbols added to certain sacred texts, especially [[lectionary]] readings of Biblical texts, as a [[mnemonic]] device to assist in their [[cantillation]].  Ekphonetic notation can take a number of forms, and has been used in several [[Jewish]] and [[Christian]] [[plainchant]] traditions, but is most commonly associated with [[Byzantine chant]].  In many cases, the original meaning of ekphonetic [[neume]]s is obscure, and must be reconstructed by comparison with later notation.

